title: golang.org: documentation examples show spell-check lines
body:
On the documentation page for package `time` (as seen [here](https://golang.org/pkg/time/#Time.Format)), example code contains what look like spell-check red underlines:

![screenshot from 2016-02-10 11 24 56](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/7328370/12953547/ee4acec6-cfe8-11e5-95fc-c3996d11469c.png)

I'm using Firefox 40.0.3
